An incredible video shows two tiny autonomous drone quadrocopters throwing and catching a pendulum by its narrow end.

Dario Brescianini, a student at ETH Zurich’s Institute for Dynamic Systems and Control, developed the complex algorithms which allow the robot quadrocopters to juggle the inverted pendulum.

The video shows one incredibly balancing the pendulum on its end as it buzzes around a lab space, then throwing it up into the air to be caught by the other.

