A major challenge was the demonstration's highly dynamic nature: the total time between the throw and catch is just over half a second, a very short time to manoeuvre the catching quadrocopters into place.

A second serious challenge the researchers faced was the high cost of failure. Failed catches tended to result in the pendulum crashing into a rotor blade, sending the quadrocopters plummeting to the ground.

'A crashed quadrocopter not only entailed repairs, but also meant recalibration of the vehicle to re-determine its operating parameters and restarting the learning algorithms,' the Robohub blog reported.

